## ✨ Features

- 🔐 Firebase Authentication (Sign Up & Login)
- 🎨 Light & Dark Mode Toggle (with localStorage)
- 📊 Dashboard showing Total Habits, Active Streak, and Completion Rate
- 📁 Habit Categories: Fitness, Meditation, Hydration, Sleep
- ✅ Habit Completion & 🔥 Streak Tracking
- 📅 Frequency Selection (Daily / Weekly / Monthly)
- 📈 Real-time Firestore syncing

## 🎯 Design Decisions & Assumptions

- Used Firebase Firestore as a serverless backend for quick development and real-time updates.
- Designed mobile-first responsive layout using vanilla CSS and grid/flexbox.
- Authentication and authorization are handled through Firebase Auth only.
- Streak and completion rate are calculated in the frontend using Firestore data.
- Minimalistic UI to keep users focused on their goals.

## ⚙️ Installation & Getting Started

### Prerequisites
- Node.js (only if you're using Firebase CLI locally)
- Firebase project set up with Firestore & Authentication enabled

### Steps

```bash
# Clone the repo
git clone https://github.com/amnraz/healthy-habit-tracker.git
cd habit-tracker/frontend

# Serve locally (use live-server or any static server)
live-server .
